description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a &lt;strong&gt;Clinical Operations Manager x2&lt;/strong&gt; (COM) in Lincolnshire. North locality. 1 x full time and 1 secondment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this role you must be an HCPC state registered paramedic with current registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting directly to the Duty Operations Manager (DOM), the COM is responsible for the efficient and effective day-to-day management and service delivery of a defined team. The COM is responsible for the supervision and management of a team of Accident and Emergency (A&amp;E) Operational staff and for ensuring the achievement of national performance targets and patient quality standards are met and upheld within their area of responsibility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The COM is responsible for the management of the station and for carrying out people management responsibilities for all team staffing issues at the local level, supporting other COMs within their locality on all aspects of people management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will ensure that the locally devolved arrangements for A&amp;E service delivery, financial management, human resources, business continuity, resilience and preparedness and local team communications operate effectively and meet the standards and targets agreed by the Divisional Director.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key result areas include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team response times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team budget and efficiency savings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sickness targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Major incident preparedness standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health and safety standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complaints resolution targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff governance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The COM will respond operationally in accordance with professional codes of conduct and Trust Policies and Procedures, undertaking the supervision of incidents in accordance with the COM Deployment Standard Operating Procedure (SOP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The COM will act as Operational Commander as required at scene. The COM will also be required to complete the full AIT training as part of the role within 12 months of appointment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will have;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to act autonomously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A desire to succeed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent people management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The attitudes and behaviours that will support our local teams in “Being the Best”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Rich Hunter, Job title: AOM, Email address: richard.hunter@emas.nhs.uk, Telephone number: 07795235904, Additional contact information: EMAS Recruitment Team, 0115 8845000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be 5 positions across the locality which may change at short notice, please call Rich Hunter for more information if required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
